<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50/5–1749: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-17T19:00:00-04:00">May 17,
                                    1949—7 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>971. Urtel 1656 May 16. Dept had assumed Deptel 918 May 12 furnished
                            sufficient authorization for action suggested final para ref tel.
                            Assuming you will keep in mind Embtel 1039 May 17 Dept authorizes you in
                            your discretion approach Nationalist milit authorities re demolitions
                            Amer properties, including utilities. If you consider desirable you
                            authorized approach your Brit and French colleagues with view their
                            taking parallel action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>